# Output punctuation

## Never use em dash

- Do **not** use the em dash character `—` (U+2014) in chat, TestRail titles/steps/expected, preview markdown, commits, or PR text.
- Prefer commas, periods, colons, parentheses, or hyphens `-` instead.

| Avoid | Use |
|-------|-----|
| Save is blocked — record is not saved | Save is blocked. Record is not saved |
| Section A — Module | Section A: Module |

## Never use semicolon

- Do **not** use `;` in chat, TestRail fields, preview markdown, commits, or PR text.
- Split into separate sentences (period), use a comma, or use a colon.

| Avoid | Use |
|-------|-----|
| Transition completes; artefact is created | Transition completes. Artefact is created |
| Role: Admin; User | Role: Admin or User |
| AC #1: save; artefact created | AC #1: save. Artefact created |

## Arrow character

- Do **not** use `→` (U+2192).
- Use `>` instead.

| Avoid | Use |
|-------|-----|
| Open Order → Documents tab | Open Order > Documents tab |
| Zoom > Full screen > Undo | Zoom > Full screen > Undo |
| `Module A → Screen B` | `Module A > Screen B` |

## Scope

Applies to QA Agent outputs: chat, TestRail cases, Shortcut comments/checklists, preview files under `.cursor/qa-memory/`.
